<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Naughty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Naughty,</orth> bad, wicked, good for nothing: <cit><quote>a n. house,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 77</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou n. varlet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 2, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this n. man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.306" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 306</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these n. times,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou n. gaoler,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so shines a good deed in a n. world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 5.91.9" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a good drum, but a n. orator,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.254" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 254</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou n. varlet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.474" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 474</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a sort of n. persons,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 167</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whiles he lived upon this n. earth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 139</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you n. mocking uncle,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 2, 26</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a n. man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 2, 26</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>thou n. knave,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>'tis a n. night to swim in,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 116</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>n. lady,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.37" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 37</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>